<subSubSection id="6DE16501251AFF9BFF45138DFEE4FC28" pageId="15" pageNumber="1630" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="2544368A251AFF9BFF45138DFEE4FC28" blockId="15.[178,1086,735,904]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1630">
Comment: The original description is based on 
<typeStatus id="FA408828251AFF9BFD2813B2FC99FD5A" box="[735,779,736,757]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1630">type</typeStatus>
material from three localities in &quot;Oku-Nikkô, 
<collectingRegion id="E73FF868251AFF9BFEA813AEFE7AFCBD" box="[351,488,764,786]" country="Japan" name="Gunma" pageId="15" pageNumber="1630">Gunma Pref.</collectingRegion>
&quot; and additional material not included in the 
<typeStatus id="FA408828251AFF9BFC3A13AFFC6BFCBD" box="[973,1017,765,786]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1630">type</typeStatus>
series from two localities in 
<collectingRegion id="E73FF868251AFF9BFE6D1248FDE9FC9F" box="[410,635,794,816]" country="Japan" name="Fukushima" pageId="15" pageNumber="1630">Fukushima Prefecture</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation id="416A4B7B251AFF9BFD7C1248FCDCFC9F" author="WATANABE Y" box="[651,846,794,816]" pageId="15" pageNumber="1630" pagination="465 - 475" refId="ref11660" refString="WATANABE Y. (2001 a): Four new species of apterous Lathrobium (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae) from Central Honshu, Japan. - Elytra, Tokyo 29 (2): 465 - 475." type="journal article" year="2001">WATANABE 2001a</bibRefCitation>
). Based on the derived morphology of the aedeagus, particularly the shape of the internal structure (basal portion strongly inflated, apical portion spine-shaped), 
<taxonomicName id="E2FB4D09251AFF9BFD3C1207FCDEFCC5" authorityName="WATANABE" authorityYear="2001" box="[715,844,852,874]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="1630" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nikkoense">
<emphasis id="178FEA98251AFF9BFD3C1207FCDEFCC5" box="[715,844,852,874]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1630">L. nikkoense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is undoubtedly closely allied to 
<taxonomicName id="E2FB4D09251AFF9BFEFC1221FEFDFC27" authorityName="HERMAN" authorityYear="2003" box="[267,367,883,904]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lathrobium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="1630" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sinense">
<emphasis id="178FEA98251AFF9BFEFC1221FEFDFC27" box="[267,367,883,904]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="1630">L. sinense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
